    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Context
    An execution context that holds parameters for an execution.
    Context.Caster<From,To>
    A functional interface representing a transformer or converter that can transform an object of type `From` into an object of type `To`.
    Context.IndexedProxy
    The interface represents a collection-like structure that allows access to elements by their positional index.
    Context.IndexedProxyFactory
    The `Indexed` interface represents a structure that mimics list-like behavior, allowing indexed access patterns.
    Context.MappedProxy
     
    Context.MappedProxyFactory
    The MapLike interface represents a structure that mimics map-like behavior, allowing key-value access patterns.
    Context.Proxy
     
    Context.ProxyFactory
    Represents a generalized collection-like structure that can act as a base for specific types of collection behaviors.
    Context.Value
    A wrapper for a contextual value.
    Executor
    An instance of the executor can execute a script.
    Logiqua
    The main interface of the Logiqua library.
    Named
    Something that is named should implement this interface.
    Named.Symbol
     
    Operation
    An operation is something that can operate on values, either evaluated or unevaluated.
    Operation.Arity
     
    Operation.Function
    A function is an operation that can be evaluated.
    Operation.Macro
    A command is an operation that can be evaluated.
    Script
    A Script object represents the AST of the calculation.
